<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 3:22PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Sherman, southeastern Dallam, northwestern Moore and northeastern
Hartley Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 322 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hartley, or 14 miles southeast of Dalhart, moving northeast at 40
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Dalhart, Hartley and Conlen.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
